{
  "texts": [
    "Genes that were predicted for differential gene expression and were found to undergo SV insertion together with log-fold changes in gene expression also all had mutated EPM regions, as well (Fig. 5c).",
    "It will be highly interesting studying insertions of, e.g.",
    "transposable elements (TEs) in non-model plant Brassicaceae species, which were associated with perturbations in gene expression relevant to the transition from C3 to C4 photosynthesis 63.",
    "Here, mining and characterisation of EPMs could improve the identification of the regulatory determinants in such evolutionary processes.",
    "We have also demonstrated that our approach is able to highlight some genotype-determined phenotypic and metabolic features of newly sequenced plants."
  ]
}